content:
@LiBin48235428 I think it is too much to argue from the details of "the timing of the staff's efforts".
I have clearly listed my views on this matter, from whether the CCP and Xi will show the internal division of the party in public, and the communication between several people is not abnormal, to the behavioral norms of the staff.
If it was Xi who ordered him to be taken out, there would not be so many details in the middle, and he could just come and take him away.

@LIamaLlamaa I beg to differ. I think people should understand the possible price of their actions. In fact, after I posted it, a large number of netizens still sent me messages expressing their support for Peng Zaizhou's actions around the world.
If we ignore these costs for the sake of so-called resistance, we are actually deceiving them.
From your perspective, this is beneficial, but as someone who shares information about resistance every day, one-sidedness makes me a demagogue.
